article_title: Kevin Counihan, The New 'Obamacare CEO,' Faces Four Key Challenges

article_metadata.author: Dan Diamond

og.description: Kevin Counihan, who had served as the head of Connecticut's health insurance exchange, on Tuesday was named the first CEO of Healthcare.gov. Counihan's mission: To make sure that the federal insurance exchange, which suffered from crippling management failures last year, runs more effectively in the second year of Obamacare coverage expansion.
